!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

tomorrow /təˈmɒrəʊ/

(tomorrows) 

1. ADV You use tomorrow to refer to the day after today. 明天 [ADV with cl] 

例： Bye, see you tomorrow. 再见，明天见。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Tomorrow is also a noun. 明天 

例： What's on your agenda for tomorrow? 你明天日程有什么安排？ 

3. ADV You can refer to the future, especially the near future, as tomorrow . 在 (尤指不久的) 将来 [ADV with cl] 

例： What is education going to look like tomorrow? 教育将来会是什么样子呢？ 

4. N-UNCOUNT Tomorrow is also a noun. 未来 [also N in pl] 

例： ...tomorrow's computer industry. …未来的计算机业。

</div>

